fields.description:
I keep getting this error message when I&#x27;m trying to access my ssh-keys page (from my profile):

{code}
#!python

Something went wrong.

This might be useful in debugging the problem:
  6eaa0675df2a44faa2e27ad0f1501dce  

{code}

Any idea what&#x27;s happening?

For instance:

{code}
#!markdown

* [Document Organization](#document-organization)
{code}

does not properly link to:

{code}
#!markdown

## Document Organization
{code}

You can see this issue in the [example markdown repository|https://bitbucket.org/tutorials/markdowndemo/overview]

I think it would be convenient if a pull request would show the commands I need to execute to get hold of the commits. That is, a field very similar to the one shown when you click "Clone" with the command:

{code}
hg pull https://bitbucket.org/<user>/<repo> -r <hash>
{code}

Right now, I work around this by clicking the small pull-from box in the header after which I see a pullrequests-branch-details-dialog with Owner, Name, Branch, and Commit. Right-clicking on "Commit" and choosing "Copy Link" gives me a link of the form

{code}
https://bitbucket.org/<user>/<repo>/commits/<hash>
{code}

which I then paste into my shell and edit to have the correct form.

I use tags in commit messages to acknowledge people that contributed.  For example,

{code}
Reported-by: Best Tester <best@tester.net>
{code}

The bitbucket website tries to linkify these addresses, but it includes the last angle bracket in the link and it adds a trailing semicolon to the commit message, yielding

bq. Reported-by: Best Tester <[best@tester.net>|mailto:best%40tester.net%3E];


Example:\\
https://bitbucket.org/petsc/petsc/commits/ed938b00aafbc8619c94f12cc845a1c4a3fa2bcd

On the page : https://bitbucket.org/dotclear/dotclear/pull-request/update/84

Java script error prevents me from updating the pr.

{code}
#!error

--
[16:19:19.354] Use of getAttributeNode() is deprecated. Use getAttribute() instead. @ https://d3oaxc4q5k2d6q.cloudfront.net/m/93c3efdfaac6/amd/build/main.js:2
[16:19:19.520] TypeError: e is null @ https://d3oaxc4q5k2d6q.cloudfront.net/m/93c3efdfaac6/amd/build/repo/index.js:6
{code}

https://bitbucket.org/api/1.0/repositories /{accountname}/{repo_slug} now returns "last_updated" and "created_on" fields with:

* &#x27;T&#x27; in the middle
* miliseconds

{code}
#!javascript
{ &#x27;last_updated&#x27;: &#x27;2013-07-22T07:48:20.023&#x27;,
  &#x27;created_on&#x27;: &#x27;2013-07-22T07:48:19.952&#x27;}
{code}

2 weeks ago (last time I ran my automation scripts) this used to return as per the spec:

https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/BITBUCKET/repository+Resource#repositoryResource-PUTarepositoryupdate

{code}
#!javascript


"last_updated": "2012-10-09 23:16:10",
    "created_on": "2012-10-09 23:14:48",
{code}

Where there is no T, or milliseconds
